	<h1>How to use job boards to win freelance work every month</h1>
	<p>In 2013 I started <a href="http://letsworkshop.com">a service that finds hundreds of freelance leads</a>. Freelancers and consultants rely on my leads to earn hundreds of thousands every year. These are leads you can find on your own for free in your own time. Here's how:</p>
	
<ol style="margin: 0;">
	
	
	<li><h2>Download my <a href="http://www.letsworkshop.com/downloads/endless_clients_cheatsheet.opml">Endless Lead Generator</a> and plug it into your favorite RSS reader.</h2>
	
	<p>This file comes pre-loaded with a huge chunk of job boards that I've collected over years. It's an OPML file so all you need to do is import into an RSS reader and you can instantly monitor almost every job board that houses freelance leads. I recommend starting with established job boards like Authentic Jobs and Behance.</p>
	
	</li>


	<li><h2>Open up your <a href="http://feedly.com">RSS reader</a> and pick the low-hanging fruit first.</h2>
	
	<p>Getting started is half the battle. Don't think you have to email as many people as possible every day. Instead, be consistent about contacting 1 or 2 every day. This will take minutes and you’ll have a constant flow of warm prospects coming into your inbox.</p>
	
	<p>Remember that ultimately it’s a numbers game, and burning out by contacting a billion leads on your first day won't produce great results. Pick the 1 or 2 low-hanging, most desirable projects to go after and contact them immediately. Later you can go back if you have time.</p> 
	
	<p>If you open up feedly and see one or two project you'd like to work on, contact those before moving on.</p></li>
	
